@NODE Requirements "System requirements - Which computers can NetMail run on?"

In order to use NetMail program, the following system requirements must
be satisfied:

 -  Amiga OS 2.1 or later (3.x suggested)
 -  screen resolution of 640 x 220 or greater (1024 x 800 suggested)
 -  a fixed width screen font such as courier or topaz for correct
    alignment of columns in tables (courier 15 suggested for 1024 x 800 screen)

 -  ZedRexx
 -  AmiTCP
 -  POP client & SMTP client
 -  UUencode & MIME encoders

 NOTE: Only ZedRexx is necessary to start NetMail.


 You may download support programs from Aminet:

 -  ZedRexx
 ZedREXX.lha        util/rexx  108K+Easily add GUI to any REXX script. V1.0c
 (Version 1.0e is available at
  HTTP://www.omnipresence.com/Amiga/Companies/RealityCheck/zrxv1r0e.lha)

 -  AmiTCP
 AmiTCP-demo-40.lha comm/tcp   738K+TCP/IP protocol stack

 -  POP client: either of AmiPOP or GetMail
 AmiPOP118.lha      comm/net    98K+Amiga POP3 Client V1.18
 GetMailSRC.lha     comm/tcp    49K+AmiTCP POP Client, receives E-Mail.
 (GetMail3.lha archive is the minimum supported)

 -  SMTP client: either of PutMail or SMTPpost
 PutMailSRC.lha     comm/tcp    57K+AmiTCP SMTP Client, Sends E-Mail.
 (PutMail3.lha archive is the minimum supported)
 IU-14-amitcp.lha   comm/tcp   392K+AmiTCP SMTP/NNTP utilities v1.4 INetUtils
 (INetUtils-1.4-AmiTCP/c/SMTPpost.amitcp)

 -  UUencoder: either of UUxT or uuIn + uuOut
 uuxt31.lha         util/arc   109K+The Best UUcoder with full WB support
 uuInOut103.lha     util/arc    17K+Very fast uuencoder and decoder
 uuOut114.lha       util/arc    10K+Very fast + smart decoder

 -  MIME Base64 encoder: either of Base64 or MMencode
 base64.lha         util/conv    3K+Base64 encoding/decoding and more V1.1
 metamail-2.3a.lha  comm/mail  210K+Send/read MIME-conformant mail.
 (metamail-2.3a/bin/mmencode)

 -  MIME Quoted-Printable encoder: MMencode
 metamail-2.3a.lha  comm/mail  210K+Send/read MIME-conformant mail.
 (metamail-2.3a/bin/mmencode)
@ENDNODE


@NODE Installation "Installation - How to install"

Installing NetMail program

   NetMail is distributed as an archive; simply decompress it and run
   the installation script. If you are a first time user you can also
   drag NetMail drawer icon anywhere in your system. Suggested place
   is in "AmiTCP:" directory.


Installing support programs

   ZedRexx and AmiTCP have their own installer scripts.
   Copy the support programs anywhere in your system; suggested place
   is in "AmiTCP:bin" directory.

   NOTE: NetMail autoconfiguration feature will find and configure support
   programs for you.
@ENDNODE


@NODE Configuration "Configuration - How to configure"

   After you have installed NetMail and support programs, double-click
   on its icon to start the program.

   NetMail has four configuration dialog windows:
     @{" Accounts  " LINK "AccountsWin.brush/main"}
     @{" Settings  " LINK "SettingsWin.brush/main"}
     @{" Drivers   " LINK "DriversWin.brush/main"}
     @{" GUI prefs " LINK "GUIPrefsWin.brush/main"}
@ENDNODE


